  "instructions": [
    "Cook the bowtie pasta according to package instructions.",
    "While pasta is cooking, heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Add cumin seeds and fennel seeds; stir until they begin to pop and emit a fragrant aroma.",
    "Add garlic cloves and onion to the pan with remaining tadka ingredients (mustard seeds if used). Stir for about 2-3 minutes until onions are translucent and spices are fragrant.",
    "Stir in curry leaves, salt to taste, and the reserved tadka seasoning mix. Cook for another minute until well combined.",
    "Drain pasta and immediately toss it with the tadka sauce while hot. Serve warm."
